This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it focuses on developing a large-scale dataset for deep reinforcement learning methods. Additionally, the paper discusses the sample inefficiency of standard deep reinforcement learning methods, which is a common problem in the field of machine learning. 

The paper also touches on the use of human demonstrations in reinforcement learning, which falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

Furthermore, the dataset is based on Minecraft, a 3D environment, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision) as computer vision techniques are often used in analyzing 3D environments. 

The paper also discusses the potential of the dataset in developing techniques to solve key research challenges within the Minecraft domain, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) as it focuses on the interaction between humans and computers. 

Finally, the paper discusses the automatic annotation of state-action pairs, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it involves natural language processing techniques.
